# Settings Module Rules

References:

- docs/product-requirements.md
- docs/database-design.md
- docs/enums.md
- docs/tech-architecture.md

---

# Module Purpose

Responsibilities:

- Business Configuration
- System Configuration
- Provider Configuration
- Feature Toggles

Settings allow business behavior changes without code changes.

---

# Core Principle

Business values must come from Settings.

Never hardcode configurable values.

---

# Examples Of Configurable Values

Cashback Percentage

Minimum Withdrawal

Maximum Withdrawal

Shopee Campaign Id

Accesstrade Provider Settings

Feature Flags

---

# Settings Storage

Suggested Entity:

SystemSetting

Fields:

- Id
- Key
- Value
- Description
- Category
- UpdatedAt
- UpdatedBy

---

# Source Of Truth

SystemSetting table is the source of truth.

Do not store business configuration in code.

---

# Settings Categories

General

Affiliate

Withdrawals

Provider

Security

FeatureFlags

---

# Cashback Settings

Examples

```text
CashbackPercentage
```

Example Value

```text
80
```

Meaning:

User receives 80% commission.

Platform keeps 20%.

---

Must be configurable.

---

# Withdrawal Settings

Examples

```text
MinimumWithdrawalAmount
MaximumWithdrawalAmount
```

---

Values should be validated.

---

# Provider Settings

Examples

```text
AccesstradeCampaignId
AccesstradeApiUrl
AccesstradeWebhookSecret
```

---

Secrets should not be exposed to frontend.

---

# Feature Flags

Examples

```text
EnableWithdrawals
EnableReferralProgram
EnableNotifications
```

---

Purpose:

Enable or disable features without deployment.

---

# Access Rules

Users

Read only selected public settings.

---

Admins

Can view and modify settings.

---

Only Admin can update settings.

---

# Validation Rules

Before saving:

Validate:

- Data Type
- Range
- Required Values

---

Examples

Cashback Percentage

Allowed:

0 - 100

---

Minimum Withdrawal

Must be:

> 0

---

Maximum Withdrawal

Must be:

> = Minimum Withdrawal

---

# Caching Rules

MVP

No caching required.

---

Future

Settings cache allowed.

Cache invalidation required after updates.

---

# Audit Rules

Every settings update must create audit log.

Store:

- Old Value
- New Value
- Updated By
- Updated At

---

Settings changes must be traceable.

---

# Security Rules

Never expose:

- API Secrets
- Webhook Secrets
- JWT Secrets
- Database Credentials

---

Frontend must never receive secret values.

---

# Required Endpoints

Admin Only

GET

/api/v1/admin/settings

---

PUT

/api/v1/admin/settings

---

# Required Commands

UpdateSystemSettingsCommand

---

# Required Queries

GetSystemSettingsQuery

---

# Frontend Rules

Settings Page

Sections:

General

Affiliate

Withdrawals

Feature Flags

---

Settings UI must:

- Validate inputs
- Show current values
- Confirm updates

---

# Testing Requirements

✓ Load settings

✓ Update settings

✓ Validation rules

✓ Audit log creation

✓ Admin authorization

✓ Secret masking

---

# Documentation Rules

If settings structure changes:

Update:

- database-design.md
- api-specification.md
- tech-architecture.md

---

# Code Generation Checklist

✓ Settings stored in database

✓ No hardcoded business values

✓ Admin-only updates

✓ Validation implemented

✓ Audit logging enabled

✓ Secrets protected

✓ Feature flags supported

Configuration belongs to Settings, not source code.
